description: The taoiseach held a press conference with European Commission president Ursula von der Leyen in Dublin.
title: Leo Varadkar calls for 'level playing field' on Brexit negotiations
title_page: Leo Varadkar calls for 'level playing field' on Brexit negotiations - BBC News
maintext: "Only as a result of that, we have a Withdrawal Agreement which assures us there is no hard border, that citizens' rights are protected and the travel area between Britain and Ireland remains in place and that the Good Friday Agreement is protected," he said.
